  "decision_conditions": [
    "The Lawson Cypress is situated within the rear garden of 7 Rogers Ruff, the majority of its canopy can be seen from the public highway and it has not been pruned before and as a result has a crown typical of this species. As a result it has a high amenity value and significantly contributes to the arboreal character of the Copse wood estate an area of special local character.",
    "Following the refusal of application 77154/TRE/2023/136 and 77154/TRE/2023/260 this new application includes a Geotechnical report by Fastrack. Although the report includes root analysis identifying a Cupressaceae species of which Cypress belongs, the roots that were found in the trial dig hole showed small roots of 1mm or less. No evidence has been provided as yet of any large roots that may be causing this type of damage.",
    "The previous application (77154/TRE/2023/260) was refused and within the Officers Report it was noted that no exploratory work had been completed to confirm the belief that the tree is respon",
    "The removal of deadwood, dangerous / hanging branches and ivy:  This does not require the formal consent of the Council."
